  <h1>Supply Chain Network Design (Martin-Beck Co.)</h1>
  <p class="muted">Selecting the best network configuration under cost and operational constraints.</p>

  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>This project analyzes the Martin-Beck Co. supply chain network design case, focusing on selecting the best network configuration under cost and operational constraints.</p>

  <h2>What I did</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Formulated the problem as an optimization model (network design / routing structure depending on the case setup)</li>
    <li>Evaluated feasible solutions and compared tradeoffs</li>
    <li>Summarized insights in a clear, decision-focused format</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Methods / Tools</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Optimization modeling</li>
    <li>Python for solving + sensitivity checking</li>
    <li>Visual summaries</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Key Results</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Identified the lowest-cost (or best objective) network design option</li>
    <li>Highlighted which constraints were binding and what drove the optimal decision</li>
    <li>Provided practical interpretation: <em>what the solution means operationally</em></li>
  </ul>

